{"data":{"markdownRemark":{"html":"<p><a href=\"https://github.com/ajwhite/jquery-stockquotes\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"jQuery Stock Quotes\">jQuery Stock Quotes</a> is a plugin that allows you to show stock symbol information. By adding a <code>data-symbol</code> attribute to the elements, you'll be able to display the stock symbol along with the latest quote.</p>\n<p>You can install this with Bower, <code>bower install jquery-stockquotes --save</code></p>\n<p>{% highlight html %}</p>\n<!-- import jQuery and the plugin -->\n<script src=\"bower_components/jquery/jquery.js\"></script>\n<script src=\"bower_components/jquery-stockquotes/dist/jquery.stockquotes.js\"></script>\n<link rel=\"stylesheet\" type=\"text/css\" href=\"bower_components/jquery-stockquotes/dist/jquery.stockquotes.css\" />\n<!-- the HTML integration -->\n<p>Twitter:  <span class=\"stock-quote\" data-symbol=\"TWTR\"></span>\nFacebook: <span class=\"stock-quote\" data-symbol=\"FB\"></span>\nGoogle:   <span class=\"stock-quote\" data-symbol=\"GOOGL\"></span>\nNetflix:  <span class=\"stock-quote\" data-symbol=\"NTFLX\"></span>\nYahoo:    <span class=\"stock-quote\" data-symbol=\"YHOO\"></span></p>\n<!-- the JS integration -->\n<script>\n$(document).on('ready', function () {\n  $('.stock-quote').stockQuotes();\n});\n</script>\n<p>{% endhighlight %}</p>\n<p>This will produce the following</p>\n<img src=\"/dist/images/labs/jquery-stockquotes.png\" alt=\"jQuery Stock Quotes\" />","frontmatter":{"date":"2015-11-15 10:30:00","permalink":"/blog/jquery-stock-quotes","title":"jQuery Stock Quotes"}}},"pageContext":{}}